	     Cape Town - A 21-year-old man has been arrested for allegedly murdering his father, Eastern Cape police said on Saturday. The son is alleged to have stabbed his 60-year-old father on Friday night at their home in Maqwathini, said Kei Bridge Police near Butterworth. The 60-year-old father died instantly, Captain Jackson Manatha said, adding that the motive behind the murder is still unclear. The suspect will appear in the Butterworth Magistrate's Court on Wednesday on a murder charge. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  